    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1887-02-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1887-02-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="465" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d465">
                <head>No. 10.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">L. S.
                                    Sackville West</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1887-02-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">February</hi> 4,
                                1887</date>. (Received February 5.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of the 3d instant, informing me that without
                            conclusion at this time of any questions which may be found to be
                            involved in the cases of seizure of British vessels in Bering Sea,
                            orders have been issued, by the President’s direction, for the
                            discontinuance of all pending proceedings, the discharge of the vessels
                            referred to, and the release of all persons under arrest in connection
                            therewith.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">L. S. Sackville
                            West.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
